aperRoundRobinConfigUpTime.name: aperRoundRobinConfigUpTime
aperRoundRobinConfigUpTime.description: This value represents the time elapsed since the server was started in 1/100nths of a second.

aperRoundRobinDomainTable.name: aperRoundRobinDomainTable
aperRoundRobinDomainTable.description: Domain information broken down domain name.

aperRoundRobinDomainEntry.name: aperRoundRobinDomainEntry
aperRoundRobinDomainEntry.description: This table contains information on each of the load balance domains under its control.

aperRoundRobinDomainName.name: aperRoundRobinDomainName
aperRoundRobinDomainName.description: The zone name for this load-balance domain.

aperRoundRobinDomainLastHostIndex.name: aperRoundRobinDomainLastHostIndex
aperRoundRobinDomainLastHostIndex.description: The host index number (from round robin node table) that was given out at the last query. A value of -1 is used to indicate that no value has ever been returned for this domain.

aperRoundRobinDomainUpServers.name: aperRoundRobinDomainUpServers
aperRoundRobinDomainUpServers.description: The number of servers that are up at this time.

aperRoundRobinDomainDownServers.name: aperRoundRobinDomainDownServers
aperRoundRobinDomainDownServers.description: The number of servers in list that are marked as down at this time.

aperRoundRobinNodeTable.name: aperRoundRobinNodeTable
aperRoundRobinNodeTable.description: Node information broken down domain name and IP address

aperRoundRobinNodeEntry.name: aperRoundRobinNodeEntry
aperRoundRobinNodeEntry.description: This table contains information on each of the machines in the different laod balance zones.

aperRoundRobinNodeName.name: aperRoundRobinNodeName
aperRoundRobinNodeName.description: The zone name for this Node.

aperRoundRobinNodeIP.name: aperRoundRobinNodeIP
aperRoundRobinNodeIP.description: The IP address of the NODE.

aperRoundRobinNodeHostIndex.name: aperRoundRobinNodeHostIndex
aperRoundRobinNodeHostIndex.description: This value is the host index within the domain. The lower the number, the higher the preference towards using the node for all name to address mappings.

aperRoundRobinNodePoolIndex.name: aperRoundRobinNodePoolIndex
aperRoundRobinNodePoolIndex.description: This value is the pool index. When all nodes with a lower index are down, the items with next highest pool index are considered for roundRobin usage.

aperRoundRobinNodeStatus.name: aperRoundRobinNodeStatus
aperRoundRobinNodeStatus.description: Indicates the status of the node. Up(1) shows that the node is up and is being considered for use. Down(2) indicates that the last query to the NODE image resulted in a down marker for the node. Admindown(3) indicates that an administrator took the node offline manually (from the UA server end). Notqueried(4) is used to indicate that a node has never been queried.

aperRoundRobinNodeResponseTime.name: aperRoundRobinNodeResponseTime
aperRoundRobinNodeResponseTime.description: Response time in MS of last node access. A value of 0 is returned if NodeStatus is not ready(1) or if the node has never been queried
